minItem.minDesc:
Seal I, White horse. Seven-horned Lamb stands on throne, opens book's first seal; four creatures 
            (angel, eagle, ox, and lion) encircle him carrying books; crowned rider on white horse below throne, holds bow and arrow; 
            John, with scroll, kneels lower center right.

Seal II, Red horse. Seven-horned Lamb stands on throne, opens book's second seal; four creatures 
            (angel, eagle, ox, and lion) encircle him carrying books; helmeted rider on red horse below throne, wields sword; 
            John seated in cave, lower right.

Seal III, Black horse. Seven-horned Lamb stands on throne, opens book's third seal; 
           four creatures (angel, eagle, ox, and lion) encircle him carrying books; crowned rider on black horse below throne, 
           holds balance; John, with scroll, kneels at right.

Seal VI, Earthquake. Seven-horned Lamb stands on throne, opens book's sixth seal; 
            darkened sun and moon overhead; crowd representing earth's inhabitants kneels in cave at left.
            John, reads scroll, seated on bench below throne at right; church in background.

Lamb, Adoration by multitude. Crowd representing earth's inhabitants stand before 
            enthroned Seven-horned Lamb, wave flowers and palm branches; a sacrifice burns beneath throne on altar; 
            John holds scroll, kneeling lower right.

False Prophet and Beast. Second Beast, resembling the Lamb (but with only two horns), emerges from the earth, center left; 
            False Prophet marks people with Beast's number, at right; those refusing to worship Beast lie dead, foreground; 
            fire falls near worshipers kneeling before image of Beast, background left.

Vial VI, Euphrates River dries up. Angel flies over river, upper left, empties contents of vial; 
            two kings, one holding a staff, wait on shore, a crowd behind them, at right; John seated in cave, lower right. 
            Vial VI, Frogs. False Prophet, Dragon, and Beast in river, lower left, with frogs emerging from their mouths.
